2"/><citedRange>462</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>86</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>190</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">mutual enmity (will arise). Monkish thinking [and] feeling it will ruin [and] there will be disregard among one another. </seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Sie werden das mönchische Denken [und] Fühlen zugrunde richten, [und] untereinander wird Nichtachtung sein.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">They will ruin monkish thinking [and] feeling, and there will be disrespect amongst themselves.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>126</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>57</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[63d] If, however, out of hate they accuse each other greatly of sins and errors; if, however, mutual respect is being lost</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[Wenn] sie jedoch (aus) Hass viel[fach] Vergehen [und] Fehler sich gegenseitig vorwerfen, ....</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">[If], however, (out of) hate, they accuse each other many [times] of offences and demerits, ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>322</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [64d] ... if the Tathāgatas cause belief, (those) will begin (to drag) the best (into the dust? and cause [it] to be ridiculed (?))</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>190</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the butter [and] sesame taste of the law (and) of the happiness of rice[alms]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [65d] ... if, however, pupils appear, who have kept up [the moral conduct], wise</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>164, 167</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [66d] (And) thereupon the Buddha spoke the three strophes of deep meaning: It has been proclaimed (by me)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>351</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>22</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he [is] the who is cutting the arrow aimed at the [not] seeing. It is you that has to act, these (Tathāgatas) are only the ones who announce</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>332</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>167, 284</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [67d] (This) strophe he spoke (first). Proclaimed to you by me earlier is the way, the one cutting the arrow of thirst</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>752</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>167</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the Tathāgatas, the omniscient ones, the wise ones. This strophe he spoke second, to strengthen these his pupils in [their] fervor.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>144</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>45</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>168</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[68d] ... (there is no other) for the purity of the mind. Those that have walked it, the ones that think, will drive away the kleśa fetter of the Māra. This (strophe he spoke third).</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The thinkers that have descended [it] will drive away the kleśa fetters of Māra.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>383</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>180</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>106</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Now this time of the law will come. [69d] What I had to proclaim to you, or what had to be taught, all this I have proclaimed to you.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>355, 402, 422f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>46</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>180</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1970a"/><citedRange>470</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2012b"/><citedRange>159</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... I have neither hidden anything, nor even have I concealed anything [and] I have never done a thing, which would (not) have been (accessible) to you.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ich verbarg weder etwas, noch auch verhüllte ich etwas, [und] nie tat ich eine Sache, welche euch (nicht zugänglich) gewesen wäre.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Neither have I hidden anything, nor even concealed anything, [and] never have I done anything that would (not) have been (accessible) to you.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>355, 402, 422</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
