            <p><note type="parallels">Uv 12.9-12.11</note><note type="philcomment" subtype="General_remarks">Includes strophes 61-70 of the first part of the Mārgavarga (XII) in a 4x17-syllable-metre (Rhythm = 6/6/5). For the situation cf. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht15"/>, <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht17"/> and <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht45"/>. Conversations between Buddha and Ānanda before Buddha’s Parinirvāṇa. The speaker here is the Buddha, addressing Ānanda. Contains the translation of Uv 12.9-12.11.</note><note type="remarks">The original manuscript is missing, but was a fragment of Ms. B, damaged in several places, approximately the right half of the leaf.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>60 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 6.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment" subtype="Transliteration">According to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>60 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 9 the reading <hi>mäsketar</hi> should be corrected to <hi>mäsketär</hi> in the transcription.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>60 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 8.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendations according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>60 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 11 and 12.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendations according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 2 and 3.</note><note corresp="#a6" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 7.</note><note corresp="#a7" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according tio <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>190</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note corresp="#a8" type="philcomment" subtype="Transliteration">According to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 9 the beginning of the line should be read as <hi>moṣ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendations according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 16 and 17.</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendations according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 19, 20, and 21.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="lingcomment"><hi>astarñeś</hi> for <hi>astaräññeśc</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 23.</note><note corresp="#b7" type="philcomment" subtype="Trancription">Emendation according to <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>61 f</citedRange></bibl>n. 27.</note></p>
